==Popular culture==
* Since 2019, [[YouTube]] has featured a chattering yellow-backed lory named "Velvet" from his home in [[India]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAFprr6PJJqENRj1ypyDcUg YouTube videos of Velvet. - accessed June 17, 2021.]</ref>{{Independent source inline|date=December 2025}}
* In May 2021, a chattering lory belonging to former [[Capcom]] sound designer [[Hideaki Utsumi]] named "Gumi" became an [[Internet meme]], with Utsumi's YouTube channel gaining over 200,000 subscribers by August, with the lory being recognized for the "wuewuewuewue" sound that it made resembling [[laughter]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCsS33cJqqykG3bM7gGDEulg |title=Hideaki Utsumi |website=[[YouTube]] |access-date=July 1, 2021 |archive-date=July 1, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210701020403/https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCsS33cJqqykG3bM7gGDEulg |url-status=live }}</ref>{{Independent source inline|date=December 2025}}

